class Solution:
    def maxValue(self, nums: List[int], k: int) -> int:
        n = len(nums)
        max_xor = 0
        for i in range(n):
            left = 0
            right = 0
            for j in range(i, n):
                left |= nums[j]
                if (j - i + 1) % 2 == 0:
                    right ^= left
                    max_xor = max(max_xor, right)
        return max_xor
```
This solution iterates over the input array and for each element, it calculates the OR of the elements to its right. It then XORs this value with the previous XOR result, updating the maximum XOR value found so far. The time complexity of this solution is O(n^2), where n is the length of the input array.

